# 8.0 Labels API (per-user)

## 8.1 ‚úîÔ∏è Register user alice123
curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/users \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "username": "alice123",
    "password": "alicepass",
    "firstName": "Alice",
    "lastName": "Test"
  }'

## 8.2 ‚úîÔ∏è Login as alice123
curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/tokens \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "username": "alice123",
    "password": "alicepass"
  }'

## 8.3 ‚úîÔ∏è Create label \"Work\" for alice123
curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/labels \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "name": "Work"
  }'
# Expected: 201 Created with { "id": 1, "name": "Work" }

## 8.4 ‚úîÔ∏è View labels as alice123
curl -i http://localhost:8080/api/labels
# Expected:
# [
#   { "id": 1, "name": "Work" }
# ]

## 8.5 ‚ùå Try to create duplicate label
curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/labels \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "name": "Work"
  }'
# Expected: 400 Bad Request with error "Label with this name already exists"

## 8.6 ‚úîÔ∏è Register user bob456
curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/users \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "username": "bob456",
    "password": "bobpass",
    "firstName": "Bob",
    "lastName": "Tester"
  }'

## 8.7 ‚úîÔ∏è Login as bob456
curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/tokens \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "username": "bob456",
    "password": "bobpass"
  }'

## 8.8 ‚úîÔ∏è View labels as bob456 (should be empty)
curl -i http://localhost:8080/api/labels
# Expected: []

